# Performance 
On my 12th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-12700F with:
- 64GB RAM
- AMD Radeon 7900 XTX (24GB VRAM)

With 10 virtual_vram_gb (DisTorch)
 *  Sampling Time: 1072 seconds (143.43s/it)
 *  Upscale Time: 65 seconds (but looks lame)
 *  Interpolation Time: 470 seconds (oops)

Note: This is the first time I have attempted to upscale to full 1080p, and it was clearly a bad idea.  Shared VRAM went up to the 3.5GB mark, and upscale was ugly.

With 12 virtual_vram_gb (and no upscale)
 *  Sampling Time: 887 seconds (143.14s/it) [i know math too]
 *  Upscale Time: N/A
 *  Interpolation Time: 40 seconds (oops)
 *  Total time (including loading all models) 995 seconds

Second run (no re-loading of models)
 *  Total time 936 seconds

# Setup

**diffusion_models** 

- [Phantom_Wan_14B-GGUF](https://huggingface.co/QuantStack/Phantom_Wan_14B-GGUF/tree/main)

**VAE**
- [wan_2.1_vae.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.1_ComfyUI_repackaged/resolve/main/split_files/vae/wan_2.1_vae.safetensors?download=true)

**Upscale Model**
- [RealESRGAN_x4plus.pth](https://huggingface.co/spaces/Marne/Real-ESRGAN/blob/main/RealESRGAN_x4plus.pth)

**Text encoders**   Chose the GGUF model (obviously)
- [umt5_xxl_fp16.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.1_ComfyUI_repackaged/resolve/main/split_files/text_encoders/umt5_xxl_fp16.safetensors?download=true)
- [umt5_xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.1_ComfyUI_repackaged/resolve/main/split_files/text_encoders/umt5_xxl_fp8_e4m3fn_scaled.safetensors?download=true)
- [umt5-xxl-encoder-gguf](https://huggingface.co/city96/umt5-xxl-encoder-gguf/tree/main)

> You can choose between fp16, fp8 and ggufs.

**CausVidLora(Optional for a lot more speed)**
- [Wan21_CausVid_14B_T2V_lora_rank32_v1_5_no_first_block.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/Wan21_CausVid_14B_T2V_lora_rank32_v1_5_no_first_block.safetensors?download=true)

(and don't be thinking that v2 might be better, it's not... not for Phantom anyway).

File save location

```
ComfyUI/
├── models/
│   ├── loras/
│   │   └─── Wan21_CausVid_14B_T2V_lora_rank32_v1_5_no_first_block.safetensors
│   ├── diffusion_models/
│   │   └─── Phantom_Wan_14B-Qx_x_x.gguf
│   ├── text_encoders/
│   │   └─── umt5-xxl-encoder-Qx_x.gguf
│   ├── upscale_models/
│   │   └─── RealESRGAN_x4plus.pth
│   └── vae/
│       └─── wan_2.1_vae.safetensors

```

# Setting DisTorch Cache

Optimal speed will be obtained by setting virtual_vram_gb to the minimum viable amount.  Think 4, 6, 8, 10gb.  You want to keep that VRAM working and full, and that Compute at near to 100%.  Shared VRAM (as observed in the Task Manager) is allowed to be used briefly, but is totally not cool.
